Implement graceful shutdown in PtyManager:

1. Enhance `killSession(id: string, force?: boolean): Promise<void>`:
   - If force=true, send SIGKILL immediately
   - Otherwise, send SIGTERM first
   - Start 5-second timeout timer
   - If process still running after 5s, send SIGKILL
   - Return promise that resolves when process fully terminated

2. Implementation details:
   ```typescript
   async killSession(id: string, force = false): Promise<void> {
     const session = this.sessions.get(id);
     if (!session) return;

     if (force) {
       session.pty.kill('SIGKILL');
     } else {
       session.pty.kill('SIGTERM');
       await this.waitForExit(id, 5000);
       if (this.sessions.has(id)) {
         session.pty.kill('SIGKILL');
       }
     }
     this.sessions.delete(id);
   }
   ```

3. Global shutdown handler:
   - `shutdownAll(): Promise<void>` for application exit
   - Hook into process SIGTERM/SIGINT for clean server shutdown
   - Gracefully terminate all sessions before server exits

